        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:13PM PDT by NWS Portland OR</headline>
        <description>At 412 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 7 miles northeast of Waldo
Lake to near East Lemolo Campground. Movement was northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Willamette Pass and Waldo Lake.

In Oregon this includes State Highway 58 between mile markers 49 and
62.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
these storms pass.</instruction>
